3E%3Cp%3EI've%20seen%20fellow%20tourists%20struggle%20to%20ask%20the%20same%20questions%20again%20and%20again%2C%20like%20how%20to%20charge%20their%20phones%20or%20whether%20they%20can%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-public-toilets-state-of-the-art-designs-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epublic%20toilets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who's%20been%20to%20over%2090%20countries%2C%20I've%20also%20encountered%20many%20of%20these%20awkward%20situations%20firsthand%20%E2%80%94%20and%20learned%20a%20lot%20of%20answers%20the%20hard%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20make%20sure%20never%20to%20travel%20abroad%20without%20knowing%20the%20answers%20to%20these%20eight%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhat%20are%20the%20public%20toilets%20like%3F%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225547%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22public%20toilet%20in%20europe%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d09477b8b41a9673fa5277%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWherever%20I%20go%2C%20I%20never%20assume%20that%20toilet%20paper%20and%20soap%20will%20be%20available%20in%20public%20bathrooms.%3Cp%3ETjeerd%20Kruse%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20traveling%2C%20I%20quickly%20learned%20that%20there%20is%20no%20one%20right%20way%20to%20use%20the%20toilet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Americans%20take%20the%20%26quot%3Bporcelain%20throne%26quot%3B%20for%20granted%2C%20but%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20it's%20common%20to%20squat%20over%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20visited%20countries%20where%20it's%20customary%20to%20pay%20an%20attendant%20a%20nominal%20amount%20for%20a%20square%20or%20two%20of%20toilet%20paper.%20In%20some%20countries'%20restrooms%2C%20you%20won't%20find%20toilet%20paper%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20but%20instead%2C%20a%20bidet%20or%20bucket%20of%20water%20to%20wipe%20yourself%20clean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20prepare%20for%20any%20and%20all%20bathroom%20situations%2C%20I%20try%20to%20bring%20a%20roll%20of%20toilet%20paper%20and%20plenty%20of%20hand%20sanitizer%20on%20every%20international%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECan%20I%20brush%20my%20teeth%20with%20tap%20water%3F%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223449%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hand%20holding%20a%20toothbrush%20under%20tap%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d094d9b8b41a9673fa5295%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222587%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhere%20I%20live%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it's%20normal%20to%20brush%20your%20teeth%20with%20tap%20water%2C%20but%20that%20isn't%20the%20case%20in%20every%20country.%3Cp%3ERomberi%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Americans%2C%20myself%20included%2C%20are%20used%20to%20turning%20on%20the%20tap%20and%20having%20fresh%2C%20clean%20water%20to%20drink%20and%20brush%20their%20teeth.%20However%2C%20this%20isn't%20the%20case%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20travel%20experiences%20have%20taught%20me%20that%20nothing%20will%20ruin%20a%20trip%20faster%20than%20gastrointestinal%20distress%20from%20unsafe%20drinking%20water.%20Now%2C%20before%20I%20travel%2C%20I%20always%20check%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravel.state.gov%2Fcontent%2Ftravel%2Fen%2Finternational-travel%2FInternational-Travel-Country-Information-Pages.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Department%20of%20State%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20see%20if%20I'll%20need%20to%20stick%20to%20bottled%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20country's%20tap%20water%20isn't%20safe%20to%20drink%2C%20I'll%20attach%20my%20toothbrush%20to%20a%20bottle%20with%20a%20rubber%20band.%20This%20helps%20me%20remember%20not%20to%20rinse%20my%20toothbrush%20under%20the%20tap%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mistake%20that's%20easy%20to%20make%20in%20the%20early%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDo%20I%20need%20to%20ap