D%20With%20India%E2%80%99s%20space%20economy%20projected%20to%20grow%20from%20%248.4%20billion%20in%202024%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Feconomy%2Feconomic-survey-2024-indian-space-sector-sees-increase-in-private-participation-300-indian-entities-file-applications%3F%5C%22%3E%2413%20billion%20by%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20country%20is%20fast%20emerging%20as%20a%20global%20space%20hub.%20Government%20reforms%20and%20increased%20private%20sector%20participation%20have%20further%20accelerated%20this%20momentum%2C%20making%20space%20innovation%20more%20accessible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20platform-in-the-making%20promises%20to%20provide%20free%20real-time%20space%20data%20to%20students%20and%20colleges%20globally%2C%20using%20just%20their%20educational%20IDs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vision%20is%20ambitious%20but%20grounded.%20If%20they%20can%20successfully%20detect%20gamma%20rays%20with%20their%20CubeSat%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feat%20no%20Indian%20entity%20has%20achieved%20%E2%80%94%20they%20plan%20to%20expand%20into%20planetary%20imaging%20CubeSats%20and%20interplanetary%20missions%2C%20offering%20affordable%2C%20sustainable%20satellite%20technology%20to%20governments%20and%20private%20players%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20Government%20or%20an%20organisation%20has%20a%20Rs%2010%20million%20budget%20for%20100%20satellites%2C%20that%20will%20be%20a%20boost%20for%20them.%20If%20you%20compare%20the%20cost%20of%20NASA%2C%20which%20is%20500%20million%20dollars%20per%20year%2C%20this%20is%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20Snehadeep%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20mentors%20who%20are%20well-versed%20in%20both%20Physics%20and%20engineering%20to%20guide%20us%20long-term.%20And%20the%20best%20mentors%20are%20from%20ISRO%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Snehadeep%2C%20highlighting%20the%20potential%20for%20India%20to%20succeed%20in%20the%20space%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20see%20space%20as%20the%20