e-image-2025-06-04T173043.061_11zon-1749104266-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-04T173043.061_11zon-1749104266-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-04T173043.061_11zon-1749104266-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FMervin-Feature-image-2025-06-04T173043.061_11zon-1749104266-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-444558%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETackling%20solid%20waste%20and%20greywater%20has%20become%20essential%20to%20protect%20these%20mangroves.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEqually%20troubling%20is%20declining%20water%20quality%2C%20fuelled%20by%20greywater%20discharge%20and%20untreated%20runoff%20from%20nearby%20human%20settlements.%20Already%20operating%20in%20harsh%2C%20saline%2C%20and%20shifting%20tidal%20conditions%2C%20mangroves%20are%20now%20burdened%20by%20pollutants%20that%20push%20sensitive%20species%20to%20the%20brink.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMangrove%20species%20like%20%3Cem%3EAvicennia%20marina%3C%2Fem%3E%20have%20adapted%2C%20but%20others%20are%20disappearing%20from%20urban%20coastlines%20altogether%2C%E2%80%9D%20Joshi%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20pressure%20of%20urban%20expansion.%20As%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s%20population%20grows%2C%20natural%20ecosystems%2C%20often%20dismissed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cunused%E2%80%9D%2C%20become%20prime%20targets%20for%20development.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20areas%20need%20to%20be%20highlighted%20and%20protected%2C%E2%80%9D%20Joshi%20urges.%20%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20not%20just%20open%20land%3B%20they%20provide%20vital%20ecosystem%20services%20that%20cities%20depend%20on.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMangroves%20may%20seem%20hardy%2C%20but%20beyond%20a%20point%2C%20degr